## ğŸ§  Coding Guidelines
RULES: Where to Place Logic
Feature	Goes In            .h?	     Goes In .cpp?	   Why?
Function Signature Only	   âœ… Yes	        âŒ No	Exposes the interface only
Full Function Body	       âŒ No	            âœ… Yes	Implementation stays private
Getters/Setters Logic	   âŒ No	            âœ… Yes	Must enforce bounds/guards
Constructor Logic	       âŒ No	            âœ… Yes	Can have side effects
Private Data Members	   âœ… Yes	        âŒ No	Must declare class shape

## ğŸ§  RULES: When To Use Getters/Setters
You Want To...	Use A Getter/Setter?
Read a private variable	                    âœ… Getter
Change a private value (with validation)	âœ… Setter
Expose something read-only	                âœ… Const Getter
Access raw array index outside class	    âŒ BAD â€” always wrap

## ğŸ§  CONTROL STRUCTURE RULES
Structure	Rule
if	        Guard-first only. No nested success logic.
while	    Must have a timeout escape + failsafe
switch	    Must use break + default: clause
for	        Must bounds-check all array accesses
continue	Only inside timing-controlled loops
return	    Used liberally for early exits (guard-first)